<TITLE> Court frames charge against Harris Chowdhury to begin trial </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 6 (bdnews24.com)- A special court in Dhaka Monday accepted the charge against Harris Chowdhury to start his trial in a case that involves illegal possession of foreign currency. Judge Syed Zahed Monsur of the Dhaka Metropolitan Special Court-9 set Aug 9 to testify witnesses. During charge-framing, the court showed Chowdhury, political secretary to former prime minister Khaleda Zia, a fugitive. The trial will proceed in his absence. The court will have to complete the trial in 45 days in line with the emergency powers rules. Joint forces raided Harris's Gulshan home and seized $2,000, 865, S$600, Tk 64,761 and a diplomatic passport on Feb 4. A case under Currency Act was filed with Gulshan Police Station against him under emergency powers rules. bdnew
